        "cooked": "<p>Yeah, as written that is also my guess. I hope they will fix it as we are also hoping for all for bigger printers <img src=\"https://forum.bambulab.com/images/emoji/twitter/sweat_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":sweat_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":sweat_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">. The objects alone are easily printable on any printer even the A1 Mini - but the generation only generates a single STL/Object.</p>",
