        "can_see_hidden_post": false,
        "can_unaccept_answer": false,
        "can_view_edit_history": true,
        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>Hey <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/pineapplebun_bbl\">@PineappleBun_BBL</a>, thx for confirming the issue.</p>\n<p>Sadly, resizing the model will not help here because as soon as the user generates a custom version it through the customizer, it will probably fail. And the error message is not helping to understand the issue.</p>\n<p>Splitting the model would also not help as it would make the process even more complicated than it is already now for the user.</p>\n<p>I am looking forward to the splitting of objects, even i do not understand how the coloring of object could affect the generation in the first place. This must be a validation step that is not necessary - as you \u201cfor now\u201d cannot send them to the printer directly.</p>",
