        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>Hi, I too would be very glad to see multiple plate support in the Parametric Model Maker. My model is specifically for breaking up a large model into printable pieces. (GRIPS: GRidfinity Interlocking basePlate System, which I can\u2019t seem to link to).</p>\n<p>I tried to make the UX for the tool as straightforward as possible, but unfortunately I had to add quite complicated instructions around how to  download/split/arrange the model. This leads to folks running into problems.</p>\n<p>Given that the 3mf export seems to already be doing an auto-arrange of the model, perhaps an easy solution for Bambu to implement would be to offer a way for the OpenSCAD script to identify which bodies should be separated. Then run the auto-arrange to place the bodies across multiple plates.</p>",
